WEBVTT

00:06.240 --> 00:07.675
[ KRS-ONE's
"Step Into A World" plays ]

00:07.708 --> 00:11.745
* Step into a world

00:11.779 --> 00:13.547
* Where there's no...

00:13.581 --> 00:15.683
Eighth grade done, son.
I made it.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.089
[ Music stops ]

00:21.122 --> 00:22.656
Can you do that again
for the camera?

00:22.690 --> 00:23.657
[ Scoffs ] No, man.

00:23.691 --> 00:24.758
And put that away.

00:24.792 --> 00:26.594
The graduation ceremony
is over.

00:26.627 --> 00:28.496
The end of
another school year.

00:28.529 --> 00:29.563
[ Door closes ]

00:29.597 --> 00:30.664
I'm have to say,

00:30.698 --> 00:31.932
I'm starting to think
moving to Orlando

00:31.965 --> 00:33.033
was a good idea.

00:33.067 --> 00:34.435
We've been here
for three years.

00:34.468 --> 00:35.936
Eddie finished
middle school...

00:35.969 --> 00:37.238
It's been a long haul

00:37.271 --> 00:38.772
since starting
on that Wednesday.

00:38.806 --> 00:40.408
Cattleman's
is going great...

00:40.441 --> 00:41.675
Well, pretty soon
Golden Saddle

00:41.709 --> 00:42.943
will be copying me
copying them.

00:42.976 --> 00:45.746
...and I just got
my biggest listing yet --

00:45.779 --> 00:47.948
a house
in Gulf Mist Estates.

00:47.981 --> 00:49.350
That fancy
gated community?

00:49.383 --> 00:50.751
Damn, woman.
Right?

00:50.784 --> 00:51.919
We should celebrate.

00:51.952 --> 00:54.054
Turn on the A.C.

00:54.088 --> 00:55.223
[ Gasps ]

00:55.256 --> 00:56.857
Evan: Yes.
O-oh!

00:56.890 --> 00:58.192
We're doing it, Jessica --

00:58.226 --> 01:00.060
We're living
the American dream,

01:00.094 --> 01:01.362
just like --
the landlord!

01:01.395 --> 01:03.264
Quick,
hide your grandmother!

01:03.297 --> 01:05.065
You still haven't
added her to the lease?

01:05.099 --> 01:06.367
No, it's 100 extra bucks
a month.

01:06.400 --> 01:07.401
Are you gonna pay it?

01:07.435 --> 01:08.969
Move, move!
Put her in the pantry!

01:09.002 --> 01:10.438
Go, go, go, go!

01:10.471 --> 01:12.873
-- Captions by VITAC --

01:12.906 --> 01:14.041
* Fresh off the boat

01:14.074 --> 01:15.709
* I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go *

01:15.743 --> 01:18.045
* If you don't know, homey,
now you know *

01:18.078 --> 01:19.280
* Fresh off the boat

01:19.313 --> 01:21.615
* Homey, you don't know
where I come from *

01:21.649 --> 01:23.083
* But I know where I'm goin'

01:23.117 --> 01:25.886
* I'm fresh off the boat

01:25.919 --> 01:27.488
**

01:27.521 --> 01:29.457
Another
debate team victory.

01:29.490 --> 01:31.425
I still haven't heard
one good reason

01:31.459 --> 01:33.594
why we shouldn't
have capital punishment.

01:33.627 --> 01:35.996
You'll never sell me
on the electric chair.

01:36.029 --> 01:38.599
That power bill
must be so high.

01:38.632 --> 01:40.901
I have to make a quick stop
to meet my new client.

01:40.934 --> 01:42.803
By all means, by all means.

01:42.836 --> 01:44.638
Whoa.

01:44.672 --> 01:46.140
This place looks nice.

01:46.174 --> 01:49.777
Eddie Murphy's mistress
lives here.
Oh.

01:49.810 --> 01:52.846
We've had a lot of trouble
trying to sell this place.

01:52.880 --> 01:55.015
It's a tough market
for high-end real estate.

01:55.048 --> 01:56.584
I'll still find you
a buyer.

01:56.617 --> 01:57.685
[ Sighs ] Okay.

01:57.718 --> 01:59.253
I like your debate blazer.

01:59.287 --> 02:00.288
The gold buttons

02:00.321 --> 02:02.190
whisper power
instead of shouting it.

02:02.223 --> 02:03.924
It's actually
my everyday blazer.

02:03.957 --> 02:05.359
I go to
St. Orlando's Prep.

02:05.393 --> 02:07.528
Private school --
Do you love it?

02:07.561 --> 02:08.862
I bet you love it.

02:08.895 --> 02:10.598
I love it.

02:10.631 --> 02:11.599
Every two years,

02:11.632 --> 02:13.767
they refresh
all of the library books

02:13.801 --> 02:15.603
so the pages
are always crisp.

02:15.636 --> 02:16.670
Girl.

02:16.704 --> 02:17.671
For real.

02:17.705 --> 02:19.207
My mom's
a librarian there.

02:19.240 --> 02:21.309
Did I mention they give us
briefcases?

02:22.343 --> 02:25.279
They have uniforms,
an amazing debate team...
Jessica: [ Sighs ]

02:25.313 --> 02:27.147
...a science lab
that is an actual lab.

02:27.181 --> 02:28.716
They even line up
for the water fountain,

02:28.749 --> 02:30.017
unlike the savages
at my school.

02:30.050 --> 02:34.121
[ All kids shouting ]

02:34.154 --> 02:35.356
Girl: [ Screams ]

02:35.389 --> 02:38.025
Can I please go to
St. Orlando's next year, Mommy?

02:38.058 --> 02:39.727
"Saint"?
Sounds expensive.

02:39.760 --> 02:42.630
But I really want to be with
a higher echelon of people.

02:42.663 --> 02:44.698
Did you just learn
the world "echelon"?

02:44.732 --> 02:46.567
Yes, and I would have
learned it sooner

02:46.600 --> 02:47.968
if I went
to St. Orlando's.

02:48.001 --> 02:49.470
Private school
is a waste of money.

02:49.503 --> 02:51.339
It's for parents
who outsource their discipline.

02:51.372 --> 02:53.574
But the private-school kids
call each other "Chum"!

02:53.607 --> 02:56.910
I don't need to pay people
to push you guys to succeed.

02:56.944 --> 02:59.012
[ Sighs ]
I already do that
myself.

02:59.046 --> 03:01.014
The Menendez brothers
went to private school,

03:01.048 --> 03:02.550
and look what happened
to them.

03:02.583 --> 03:03.484
Who are they?

03:03.517 --> 03:04.652
Doesn't matter.

03:04.685 --> 03:06.654
The important thing is

03:06.687 --> 03:08.989
they didn't
get away with it.

03:09.022 --> 03:11.559
**

03:11.592 --> 03:12.893
Check out my new weapon

03:12.926 --> 03:15.363
against the scourge
of dead palm fronds --

03:15.396 --> 03:18.198
my telescopic pruner.

03:18.232 --> 03:19.900
Mm! Heh.
[ Laughs ]

03:19.933 --> 03:21.168
I'll tell ya.

03:21.201 --> 03:23.036
The right tool
can make yard work a hoot.
Hmm.

03:23.070 --> 03:26.073
[ Laughs ]
I've always dreamed of owning
a sit-down lawn mower.

03:26.106 --> 03:27.441
I'd cut grass,

03:27.475 --> 03:29.510
reenact scenes from
"Can't Buy Me Love"...

03:29.543 --> 03:30.678
Well, do it.

03:30.711 --> 03:31.745
Your restaurant's
doing well.

03:31.779 --> 03:32.680
You can afford one.

03:32.713 --> 03:34.515
My yard doesn't
belong to me.

03:34.548 --> 03:35.516
I rent.

03:35.549 --> 03:36.950
I can't pluck a dandelion

03:36.984 --> 03:39.353
without hearing about it
from my landlord Murray.

03:39.387 --> 03:41.221
I can't wait
to be a homeowner.

03:41.255 --> 03:42.856
A man should own
his own house.

03:42.890 --> 03:44.057
Murray's open to selling,

03:44.091 --> 03:45.726
but Jessica and I
are very strict

03:45.759 --> 03:46.960
about our long-term plans.

03:46.994 --> 03:49.062
We agreed for
the next three years

03:49.096 --> 03:51.899
we reinvest everything
into our businesses.

03:52.433 --> 03:53.701
[ Crunch ]

03:53.734 --> 03:54.802
Oh, man!

03:54.835 --> 03:58.205
That was Honey's
favorite flamingo.

03:58.238 --> 03:59.773
She's gonna be P.O.'d.

03:59.807 --> 04:00.708
Aw.

04:00.741 --> 04:02.343
[ Door bell chimes ]

04:04.244 --> 04:05.379
Hey.

04:05.413 --> 04:06.547
Evan said
he'd pay for my manicure

04:06.580 --> 04:07.915
if I talked to you
about St. Orlando's.

04:07.948 --> 04:10.418
I'm an alumna -- I --

04:10.451 --> 04:12.219
Evan: Will you please
hear her out?

04:12.252 --> 04:14.455
I know private school
is expensive,

04:14.488 --> 04:16.423
but we only
have to send me.

04:17.491 --> 04:19.125
The "Others"
don't need to know.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.095
Come with me.

04:23.196 --> 04:26.734
These...are life plans.

04:26.767 --> 04:28.902
I made one
for each member of the family,

04:28.936 --> 04:30.904
and I update them
every five years.

04:30.938 --> 04:33.407
I've mapped out
all the classes and experiences

04:33.441 --> 04:37.144
you boys need to be successful
and lead good lives.

04:37.177 --> 04:39.012
Emery's good
at so many things,

04:39.046 --> 04:40.848
so I left
his career plan open,

04:40.881 --> 04:43.784
and I focused on
his personal life.

04:43.817 --> 04:46.854
Eddie's plan was easy
because the goal was simple.

04:46.887 --> 04:49.457
* Yeah

04:49.490 --> 04:50.958
And here is your plan.

04:52.793 --> 04:55.295
I've thought of everything.

04:55.329 --> 04:57.798
I've already seen
these boards.
What do you mean?

04:57.831 --> 04:59.667
I use the garage
as a cartwheel zone

04:59.700 --> 05:01.535
when I want to express joy
in private.

05:01.569 --> 05:03.671
But I wasn't planning on you
finding them

05:03.704 --> 05:04.772
for another two years.

05:04.805 --> 05:06.940
You're ahead of schedule.

05:06.974 --> 05:09.610
And I'm ahead of everyone
in my class, too.

05:09.643 --> 05:11.845
That's why I want to go
to St. Orlando's.

05:11.879 --> 05:13.947
I could just give you
more C.L.C.

05:13.981 --> 05:16.049
I've already done
all the workbooks --

05:16.083 --> 05:18.018
even the French one.

05:18.051 --> 05:20.454
[ Speaks French ]

05:20.488 --> 05:24.858
**

05:24.892 --> 05:26.159
Jessica: You have five minutes
to convince me

05:26.193 --> 05:27.695
why private school's
better for my son

05:27.728 --> 05:28.829
than public school.

05:31.865 --> 05:33.434
I'll only need four.

05:35.335 --> 05:38.305
Eddie: Emery, that squirrel
was on the porch again.

05:38.338 --> 05:40.173
We need to bean him in the head
with your marbles.

05:40.207 --> 05:41.509
[ Mouse clicking ]

05:41.542 --> 05:42.810
Is that a Pentium II?
Yep.

05:42.843 --> 05:44.845
I borrowed it form the A/V club
for the summer.

05:44.878 --> 05:45.879
Check it out,

05:45.913 --> 05:47.147
I'm editing
your graduation video.

05:47.180 --> 05:49.182
We are gathered
 to say goodbye

05:49.216 --> 05:51.719
[Voice breaking]
 to the glass of 1997.

05:53.053 --> 05:54.555
Whoa,
it's like "Pop Up Video"!

05:54.588 --> 05:55.889
Isn't it cool?

05:55.923 --> 05:58.492
As the great Boyz II Men
 once said,

05:58.526 --> 06:01.762
"It's so hard to say goodbye
 to yesterday."

06:03.797 --> 06:05.433
[ Clicks ]
So funny, right?

06:07.468 --> 06:08.168
Sure.

06:08.201 --> 06:09.069
Snack break --

06:09.102 --> 06:10.070
You guys want anything?

06:10.103 --> 06:11.204
You know we do.

06:13.273 --> 06:14.742
You guys want to have
some fun?

06:14.775 --> 06:16.243
-Yeah.
-Mm-hmm.

06:17.778 --> 06:20.347
Lou, I've been thinking
about what you said.

06:20.380 --> 06:21.715
About dandelions?
I know.

06:21.749 --> 06:23.350
I regret sharing that
with you.

06:23.383 --> 06:24.351
It felt very personal.

06:24.384 --> 06:25.419
No, no, no.

06:25.453 --> 06:27.187
About you wanting
to own your own house.

06:27.220 --> 06:28.922
I have a friend
that can help you

06:28.956 --> 06:30.290
free up some cash.

06:30.323 --> 06:32.893
He's outside right now
waiting for my signal.

06:33.794 --> 06:35.395
Now!

06:35.429 --> 06:38.466
[ Soft music plays ]

06:44.672 --> 06:45.639
Oh, my God.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

06:45.673 --> 06:46.740
Michael Bolton.

06:46.774 --> 06:47.875
[ Chuckles nervously,
clears throat ]

06:47.908 --> 06:49.076
Um, what are you
doing here?

06:49.109 --> 06:50.711
Recording my new album
in Orlando.

06:50.744 --> 06:54.448
I got to be in Florida
183 days out of the year

06:54.482 --> 06:56.083
for tax purposes.

06:56.116 --> 06:58.552
Savvy in
 and out of the studio.

06:58.586 --> 07:00.287
[ Chuckles ]

07:00.320 --> 07:02.322
I've got a proposal
for you.

07:02.355 --> 07:04.558
Do you know how many women
would kill to hear me say that?

07:04.592 --> 07:06.059
So many women!

07:06.093 --> 07:07.094
My wife for one.

07:07.127 --> 07:08.496
[ Chuckles ]

07:08.529 --> 07:10.964
Jessica: I already pay taxes
for public school.

07:10.998 --> 07:14.902
Why would I spend an extra
four grand a year on private.

07:14.935 --> 07:16.069
Well, first of all,

07:16.103 --> 07:18.405
St. Orlando's
is a year-round school.

07:18.438 --> 07:20.173
No summer vacation?

07:20.207 --> 07:21.509
I could just stick my kids

07:21.542 --> 07:23.176
in public summer school
for free.

07:23.210 --> 07:26.680
Certainly, but half the kids
are forced to be there

07:26.714 --> 07:29.483
because they're, forgive me,
"Dum-dums."

07:29.517 --> 07:30.818
Is that really
what you want?

07:30.851 --> 07:32.986
Well, what I don't want
is to help pay

07:33.020 --> 07:34.988
for your school's
football program.

07:35.022 --> 07:36.089
There's no football here.

07:36.123 --> 07:37.658
We teach only
the "Networking" sports --

07:37.691 --> 07:40.961
golf, squash, birding.

07:40.994 --> 07:42.262
That's great.

07:42.295 --> 07:44.164
But I'm sure the teachers here
are just as lazy.

07:44.197 --> 07:45.499
Oh,
we don't have teachers.

07:45.533 --> 07:47.601
We hire specialists
in their field.

07:47.635 --> 07:49.336
We call them
"Consultants."

07:49.369 --> 07:51.639
Continue.
We're private,

07:51.672 --> 07:53.607
so we can easily fire

07:53.641 --> 07:55.375
any underperforming
consultants.

07:56.810 --> 07:57.878
[ Exhales sharply ]

07:57.911 --> 08:00.280
Did I mention that
99% of our students

08:00.313 --> 08:02.149
go on
to Ivy League schools?

08:02.182 --> 08:04.117
The other 1%
go straight to med school.

08:04.151 --> 08:06.954
The first step
to doctor-president.

08:06.987 --> 08:09.557
We have relationships
with all the top universities.

08:09.590 --> 08:10.991
We send more kids
to Harvard

08:11.024 --> 08:12.626
than any other school
in Orlando.

08:12.660 --> 08:13.794
And with a student

08:13.827 --> 08:15.863
who is already
academically strong,

08:15.896 --> 08:16.964
like your son?

08:16.997 --> 08:19.232
We could send him
into the stratosphere.

08:23.436 --> 08:25.305
The astronaut
holding the camera

08:25.338 --> 08:27.040
is also
a St. Orlando's alum.

08:30.277 --> 08:31.712
One tuition, please.

08:31.745 --> 08:32.846
Yes!

08:32.880 --> 08:34.081
Goodbye, Mommy.

08:34.114 --> 08:36.082
Tell the family
I'll see them in six months.

08:36.116 --> 08:37.650
W-We're not
a boarding school.

08:37.684 --> 08:38.852
Ah.

08:45.693 --> 08:47.360
I'll pay for everything
but P.E.

08:47.394 --> 08:49.597
Evan can just learn tennis
from his brother.

08:49.630 --> 08:50.698
We can't do that.

08:50.731 --> 08:52.032
Okay, fine.

08:52.065 --> 08:54.267
I'll pay for P.E.,
but no English.

08:54.301 --> 08:56.236
He gets that free
from life.

08:56.269 --> 08:58.839
We don't offer private school
Ã  la carte.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.373
I'll pay
the whole year up front,

09:00.407 --> 09:01.374
but you have to give me

09:01.408 --> 09:02.943
a substantial
early-bird discount.

09:02.976 --> 09:05.012
It's not that simple.

09:05.045 --> 09:07.715
First your son must be
accepted into this school.

09:07.748 --> 09:09.683
There is an application.

09:09.717 --> 09:10.550
Okay, sure. Whatever.

09:10.584 --> 09:11.852
I'll fill it out
right now.

09:11.885 --> 09:13.721
It's more involved
than that.

09:13.754 --> 09:15.889
We need
letters of recommendation,

09:15.923 --> 09:18.025
transcripts,
an interview.

09:18.058 --> 09:19.392
We're highly selective.

09:19.426 --> 09:20.493
But...

09:21.762 --> 09:23.731
...Diversity.

09:23.764 --> 09:25.265
Oh, we don't have to worry
about that here.

09:25.298 --> 09:26.233
We're private.

09:26.266 --> 09:28.568
So,
I have to earn the privilege

09:28.602 --> 09:30.804
to pay
your ridiculous tuition?

09:32.072 --> 09:33.941
If my son
doesn't get into Harvard,

09:33.974 --> 09:35.743
I want a full refund.

09:38.779 --> 09:40.547
Headmaster.

09:40.580 --> 09:44.217
**

09:44.251 --> 09:45.819
You want to buy
my restaurant?

09:45.853 --> 09:47.420
Well, I've already
conquered music,

09:47.454 --> 09:49.422
and it's time to diversify
my brand.

09:49.456 --> 09:51.424
And Kenny Rogers
is doing so well

09:51.458 --> 09:53.426
with his
chicken restaurants --

09:53.460 --> 09:54.594
so well.

09:54.628 --> 09:56.630
He never lets you forget.

09:56.664 --> 09:57.831
I carry this around with me

09:57.865 --> 09:59.767
just to give me
motivation.

10:00.333 --> 10:02.502
[ Sleigh bells jingle ]

10:02.535 --> 10:04.638
Hmm.

10:06.206 --> 10:08.508
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

10:08.541 --> 10:09.509
Well, I'm flattered,

10:09.542 --> 10:11.144
but my restaurant's
not for sale.

10:11.178 --> 10:13.413
I moved my whole family
down here for this,

10:13.446 --> 10:14.614
put a lot of work into it.

10:14.648 --> 10:15.683
I built it from nothing.

10:15.716 --> 10:17.617
What if I come in
as a silent partner?

10:17.651 --> 10:19.486
You could still
run the day-to-day,

10:19.519 --> 10:21.021
I'd get
a stake of the company,

10:21.054 --> 10:22.589
and you get
a big cash infusion.

10:22.622 --> 10:26.126
Which you can use
to buy your house.

10:26.159 --> 10:27.094
Ayy!

10:27.127 --> 10:28.128
Hmm.

10:28.161 --> 10:29.429
That does sound like
a good deal.

10:29.462 --> 10:31.264
But Jessica and I
have a rule --

10:31.298 --> 10:33.300
We don't deviate
from our life plan.

10:33.333 --> 10:35.335
And it's worked out well
for us so far.

10:35.368 --> 10:36.436
[ Sighs ]

10:36.469 --> 10:37.838
Sorry,
but the answer is no.

10:38.872 --> 10:39.873
[ Exhales sharply ]

10:39.907 --> 10:42.042
Michael, I am so sorry.

10:42.075 --> 10:43.977
I don't know what happened.

10:44.011 --> 10:45.946
I'm s--
I don't know what happened.

10:45.979 --> 10:47.314
It's okay.

10:47.347 --> 10:48.348
It was worth a shot.

10:48.381 --> 10:50.017
How do you guys
even know each other?

10:50.050 --> 10:52.185
Oh, I did some
emergency dental work on him

10:52.219 --> 10:54.054
during his
Time, Love & Tenderness tour.

10:54.087 --> 10:55.288
Oh.

10:55.322 --> 10:56.824
I slipped on a bouquet
of white roses.

10:56.857 --> 10:58.391
**

10:58.425 --> 10:59.559
[ Computer bleeps ]

10:59.592 --> 11:01.361
[ Laughter ]

11:01.394 --> 11:02.562
Dave:
It's not funny, dude.

11:02.595 --> 11:04.564
[ Laughter ]

11:04.597 --> 11:05.899
I always wear underwear.
Look.

11:07.000 --> 11:09.336
Oh. No. Never mind.

11:09.369 --> 11:11.004
What's going on?

11:11.038 --> 11:12.840
We're turning
your boring gradation video

11:12.873 --> 11:14.107
into gold.

11:14.875 --> 11:17.878
[ Laughter ]

11:19.747 --> 11:21.614
[ Laughter ]

11:23.216 --> 11:24.584
[ Laughter ]

11:26.887 --> 11:28.488
[ Laughter ]

11:28.521 --> 11:30.023
Trent, I can't believe
you're a Sparrow Scout.

11:30.057 --> 11:30.891
That's so lame.

11:30.924 --> 11:32.192
I know
how to filet a trout.

11:32.225 --> 11:33.393
What can you filet?

11:33.426 --> 11:35.362
You know I don't eat
anything that has a mama.

11:35.395 --> 11:37.364
[ Computer bleeps ]
Brian: Wait, what?

11:37.397 --> 11:39.032
What the hell is this?

11:39.767 --> 11:42.002
[ Laughter ]

11:42.035 --> 11:43.703
Who wrote this bubble?

11:43.737 --> 11:44.872
Who thinks this?

11:44.905 --> 11:46.206
No, I want to know.

11:46.239 --> 11:49.276
**

11:49.309 --> 11:52.045
We should probably update this
to include private school.

11:52.079 --> 11:53.580
Should I get
the Wite-Out?

11:53.613 --> 11:56.116
In this family,
we don't hide mistakes.

11:56.149 --> 11:58.051
We look at them,
feel shame,

11:58.085 --> 12:00.220
and never talk about them
again.

12:00.253 --> 12:01.755
Hey, what are you guys
doing out here?

12:01.789 --> 12:04.524
I'm just showing Evan
our life plans.

12:04.557 --> 12:05.592
Oh, great.

12:05.625 --> 12:06.894
You know,
I was just thinking about

12:06.927 --> 12:08.028
how well
we've done with those.

12:08.061 --> 12:09.562
Yes, because
we're very strict

12:09.596 --> 12:10.931
about sticking
to the plan.

12:10.964 --> 12:12.900
Uh, we sure are.
[ Laughs ]

12:12.933 --> 12:14.301
Never stray no matter what.

12:14.334 --> 12:15.903
Otherwise, what's the point
of a plan, right?

12:15.936 --> 12:17.370
Right.

12:17.404 --> 12:18.305
[ Chuckles ]

12:19.439 --> 12:21.074
Uh, Evan, I don't know
if your mom mentioned this,

12:21.108 --> 12:22.242
but I did
all the collage work.

12:22.275 --> 12:23.977
I didn't.

12:24.011 --> 12:25.112
I didn't.

12:25.946 --> 12:27.614
Hmm.

12:30.617 --> 12:32.285
You're not gonna tell him
about private school?

12:32.319 --> 12:33.921
Not yet.

12:33.954 --> 12:35.322
Let's get you in first.

12:35.355 --> 12:37.390
If I'm gonna stray
from the plan,

12:37.424 --> 12:38.926
it can't be
for just a "Maybe."

12:38.959 --> 12:41.094
[ Notorious B.I.G.'s
"Mo Money Mo Problems" plays ]

12:41.128 --> 12:43.663
Evan got a kangaroo sticker
in math.

12:43.696 --> 12:45.232
Does kangaroo mean "A"?

12:45.265 --> 12:47.067
We don't believe
in letter grades.

12:47.100 --> 12:48.768
Well, St. Orlando's does,

12:48.802 --> 12:50.170
so if you had to say

12:50.203 --> 12:53.006
what grade
a kangaroo represents,

12:53.040 --> 12:55.075
would you say "A"?

12:55.108 --> 12:57.110
I'd say a "B."

12:57.144 --> 12:59.146
* Can't no PhD hold me down

12:59.179 --> 13:00.480
"A"?
* Cudda schooled me
to the game *

13:00.513 --> 13:01.781
* Now I know my duty

13:01.815 --> 13:03.116
* Stay humble, stay low,
blow like Hootie *

13:03.150 --> 13:04.784
Your daughter attends
St. Orlando's, right?

13:04.818 --> 13:06.453
As the parent
of a current student,

13:06.486 --> 13:08.121
I need you to sign
this letter of recommendation

13:08.155 --> 13:09.489
I wrote for my son.
* I don't know what
they want from me *

13:09.522 --> 13:12.259
I will if you lower
your commission.

13:12.292 --> 13:13.293
* It's like the mo' money
we come across *

13:13.326 --> 13:16.196
* The mo' problems we see

13:16.229 --> 13:17.865
You're an alumna
of St. Orlando's, right?

13:17.898 --> 13:19.332
I need you to sign
this letter of recommendation

13:19.366 --> 13:20.300
I wrote for my son.

13:20.333 --> 13:22.035
Oh, I really
can't sign anything

13:22.069 --> 13:23.603
with my nails
so jacked up.

13:23.636 --> 13:25.705
* I'm the D to the A
to the D-D-Y *

13:25.738 --> 13:27.941
* I Know you'd rather see me die
than to see me fly *

13:27.975 --> 13:30.310
* I call all the shots,
rip all the spots *

13:30.343 --> 13:32.145
* Rock all the rocks,
cop all the drops *

13:32.179 --> 13:33.513
So we agree.

13:33.546 --> 13:35.182
We pool our graduation money

13:35.215 --> 13:37.184
so we can turn
this driveway into a gym.

13:37.217 --> 13:38.685
We'll have all summer
to get ripped.

13:38.718 --> 13:40.153
We show up to high school
yoked out,

13:40.187 --> 13:41.788
and people will think
we're sophomores.

13:41.821 --> 13:44.291
I know a great
preacher curl workout.

13:44.324 --> 13:45.725
Two of my sisters
work at GNC,

13:45.758 --> 13:47.560
so I can hook us up
with some creatine.

13:47.594 --> 13:49.696
It's really
coming together.

13:49.729 --> 13:51.398
My step-brother
has the video.

13:51.431 --> 13:53.566
What?
I took it home
last night

13:53.600 --> 13:55.335
to work on some more
mean bubbles about you guys,

13:55.368 --> 13:56.403
and he found it
in my room.

13:56.436 --> 13:58.005
That dude is a tool.

13:58.038 --> 13:59.539
He's gonna show the tape
to everyone.

13:59.572 --> 14:01.674
It won't matter how buff I am
when we start school

14:01.708 --> 14:03.310
if people know
I'm a Sparrow Scout.

14:03.343 --> 14:05.678
People will think
I want to do it with a tree.

14:05.712 --> 14:06.713
I'm ruined.

14:06.746 --> 14:08.048
I was gonna
go out for football.

14:09.616 --> 14:11.184
I just want your support
on this.

14:11.218 --> 14:12.852
Which part, man?

14:12.886 --> 14:14.687
We have to get
that tape back.

14:14.721 --> 14:16.789
We can't start high school
as losers.

14:18.858 --> 14:21.361
This is the interview portion
of our process.

14:21.394 --> 14:23.563
We just have a few questions
to ask you.

14:23.596 --> 14:24.764
It's my pleasure.

14:24.797 --> 14:27.767
So, Evan, what's a current item
in the news

14:27.800 --> 14:28.868
that interests you?

14:28.902 --> 14:30.203
Sheep cloning.

14:30.237 --> 14:32.505
I think it would be a boon
for the sweater industry.

14:32.539 --> 14:33.540
Who do you admire?

14:33.573 --> 14:35.808
Whom do I admire?

14:37.978 --> 14:39.947
Why are you interested
in our school?

14:39.980 --> 14:41.614
I'd come for your blazers,

14:41.648 --> 14:42.615
but I'd stay for your

14:42.649 --> 14:44.384
International
Baccalaureate program.

14:45.785 --> 14:46.920
Tell me about your family.

14:46.954 --> 14:48.355
They're all good eggs.

14:48.388 --> 14:50.457
We rent a house
in North Orlando,

14:50.490 --> 14:52.125
my parents
run a steakhouse.

14:52.159 --> 14:53.793
We're just your typical
American family

14:53.826 --> 14:55.562
who's overcome
incredible odds

14:55.595 --> 14:56.529
to achieve big dreams.

14:56.563 --> 14:59.466
[ Chuckles ]

14:59.499 --> 15:02.035
Well,
that's all of our questions.

15:02.069 --> 15:03.470
No red flags.

15:03.503 --> 15:04.737
[ Inhales sharply ]

15:04.771 --> 15:06.306
We'll be in touch with you
very soon.

15:06.339 --> 15:07.574
**

15:07.607 --> 15:09.176
[ Whispering ]
Hey, great job.

15:12.012 --> 15:13.947
Evan, it's here.

15:14.514 --> 15:16.416
It's so big!

15:16.449 --> 15:18.251
That means they're sending us
parking instructions,

15:18.285 --> 15:20.887
reading lists,
bumper stickers for the car...

15:20.920 --> 15:24.591
"Dear Mr. Huang,
sorry to inform you that"...

15:24.624 --> 15:25.825
The hell?!

15:25.858 --> 15:28.261
Oh, you didn't get in?

15:31.464 --> 15:33.600
And they still sent us these?

15:39.339 --> 15:41.074
How could you not get in?

15:41.108 --> 15:43.410
You have perfect grades,
you killed your interview,

15:43.443 --> 15:45.478
and there is no way they
could tie you back to Eddie.

15:45.512 --> 15:48.115
Well, I guess they don't think
I belong in their echelon.

15:48.148 --> 15:51.418
No.
Someone made a mistake.

15:51.451 --> 15:52.785
[ Knocks at door ]

15:55.055 --> 15:56.423
You messed up, Deidre.

15:56.456 --> 15:58.625
Evan didn't
get into St. Orlando's.

15:58.658 --> 16:00.427
It was your
letter of recommendation.

16:00.460 --> 16:01.661
Uh, you mean
the one that you wrote

16:01.694 --> 16:02.695
and I just signed?

16:02.729 --> 16:05.965
W-- It was not
a strong signature!

16:05.999 --> 16:08.801
It tapered off at the end,
conveying doubt.

16:08.835 --> 16:11.371
Jessica, look,
private schools are picky.

16:11.404 --> 16:14.507
Unless your family
has gone there for generations,

16:14.541 --> 16:16.543
or you're the child
of someone who works there,

16:16.576 --> 16:18.378
there's really
no guarantee.

16:18.411 --> 16:20.680
But Evan
is overqualified.

16:20.713 --> 16:21.981
How could
they reject him?

16:22.015 --> 16:23.683
Maybe it's not him.

16:23.716 --> 16:25.118
Maybe it's you.

16:25.152 --> 16:27.654
These schools don't just
evaluate the student.

16:27.687 --> 16:29.322
They evaluate
the whole family.

16:29.356 --> 16:32.325
Why would my family
be rejected?

16:32.359 --> 16:33.993
We're doing great.

16:34.027 --> 16:35.662
We live
in a good neighborhood,

16:35.695 --> 16:37.197
we own
our own restaurant --

16:37.230 --> 16:39.232
Word in
the birding community --

16:39.266 --> 16:41.668
St. Orlando's
saw you as renters

16:41.701 --> 16:45.038
who work
in the service industry.

16:45.072 --> 16:46.173
And I heard sometimes

16:46.206 --> 16:48.007
you hide you mother-in-law
in the pantry?

16:48.041 --> 16:49.442
Mm.

16:50.009 --> 16:51.311
[ Car door closes ]

16:51.344 --> 16:52.645
Murray,
what are you doing here?

16:52.679 --> 16:54.081
I already sent you
this month's rent.

16:54.114 --> 16:56.716
Ah,
just inspecting my property,

16:56.749 --> 16:57.850
and I happen to notice

16:57.884 --> 16:59.752
that there's some damage
to the driveway

16:59.786 --> 17:01.221
which I'm gonna
have to charge you for.

17:01.254 --> 17:04.022
Did you have
an above-ground pool out here

17:04.057 --> 17:05.092
or something?

17:05.125 --> 17:07.359
We did not.

17:07.394 --> 17:09.229
And I notice that the lawn
looks a little different.

17:09.262 --> 17:10.530
Have you been
tampering with it?

17:10.563 --> 17:11.864
What? No.

17:11.897 --> 17:14.166
Well, someone's been
weeding this yard,

17:14.201 --> 17:15.602
'cause I don't see
any dandelions.

17:15.635 --> 17:16.935
You know they help indicate

17:16.969 --> 17:19.205
whether the grass
is getting enough moisture,

17:19.239 --> 17:21.241
so someone better not
be messing with them.

17:22.242 --> 17:23.876
[ Inhales sharply ]

17:23.910 --> 17:25.278
You know what, Murray?

17:25.311 --> 17:26.713
I did pick the dandelions.

17:26.746 --> 17:28.348
I picked 10 dandelions,

17:28.381 --> 17:29.249
and I made 10 wishes,

17:29.282 --> 17:30.550
and you know
what they all were?

17:30.583 --> 17:32.018
To own my own house.

17:32.051 --> 17:34.554
You know, you don't have
to keep making the same wish

17:34.587 --> 17:35.888
over and over.

17:35.922 --> 17:37.424
God hears you
after the first one.

17:37.457 --> 17:38.791
[ Sighs ]

17:38.825 --> 17:40.527
**

17:40.560 --> 17:42.929
[ Video plays,
Tyler laughs ]

17:46.333 --> 17:48.968
Are you sure
your step-brother's only 16?

17:49.001 --> 17:50.103
No. Tyler could be 30.

17:50.137 --> 17:51.638
I don't know
much about him.

17:51.671 --> 17:54.641
I'm just gonna go talk to him,
young man to young man --

17:54.674 --> 17:56.576
ask him to remember
what it was like

17:56.609 --> 17:57.777
when he was a freshman,

17:57.810 --> 17:59.546
how hard it was
starting high school

17:59.579 --> 18:01.148
when all you have
is your friends

18:01.181 --> 18:04.083
and how I'm asking,
as Brian's friend,

18:04.117 --> 18:05.418
for that tape back.

18:05.452 --> 18:07.420
[ Inspirational music plays ]

18:07.454 --> 18:08.721
[ Music stops ]
Well, that'll never work.

18:08.755 --> 18:10.757
Yeah, put that
in the "Stupid idea" file.

18:10.790 --> 18:12.925
You guys are too quick
with that file.

18:12.959 --> 18:15.795
I don't know why my
"Poison him" idea
is in there.

18:15.828 --> 18:17.997
Unless someone
comes up with a better plan,

18:18.030 --> 18:19.299
I'm going in.

18:21.801 --> 18:24.771
[ Door opens, closes ]
[ Laughs ]

18:24.804 --> 18:26.973
[ Knocks at door ]

18:27.006 --> 18:29.609
Mom, I don't want
any muesli.

18:31.878 --> 18:33.513
I recognize you
from the video.

18:33.546 --> 18:34.614
Your pop-up said

18:34.647 --> 18:35.782
you ate string cheese
that fell in the gutter.

18:35.815 --> 18:37.584
It was lying
on a bed of leaves.

18:37.617 --> 18:39.619
It was clean.
What are you doing here?

18:39.652 --> 18:41.788
I'm one of your
step-brother's friends.

18:41.821 --> 18:43.456
I'm here to talk to you
young man to young man,

18:43.490 --> 18:45.258
and to ask you to remember
what it was like

18:45.292 --> 18:46.493
when you were
a freshman --

18:46.526 --> 18:47.927
[ Glass shatters ]

18:47.960 --> 18:49.529
-What the hell?
-Get the tape!

18:52.332 --> 18:53.533
Poison him
before you leave!

18:53.566 --> 18:56.636
**

19:00.173 --> 19:01.641
Nope.

19:02.742 --> 19:03.876
Nope.

19:05.144 --> 19:06.145
What's this
two-tone one?

19:06.179 --> 19:07.647
They're all the same,
Michael.

19:08.981 --> 19:10.483
Okay, let's do it.

19:10.517 --> 19:11.684
Is my receptionist
not out there?

19:11.718 --> 19:12.785
Rebecca!

19:12.819 --> 19:14.687
I don't care if it's not
in my life plan.

19:14.721 --> 19:16.122
I can't be a renter
anymore.

19:16.155 --> 19:17.156
I need to own my house,

19:17.190 --> 19:19.025
so I'll sell you
a stake in the restaurant

19:19.058 --> 19:20.460
and take you on
as a partner.

19:20.493 --> 19:22.562
And together,
we'll destroy Kenny Rogers.

19:22.595 --> 19:24.831
That's more your thing,

19:24.864 --> 19:26.733
but I like that
you're motivated by revenge.

19:26.766 --> 19:27.834
My wife will love that.

19:29.502 --> 19:31.504
[ All chuckling ]

19:31.538 --> 19:34.874
Mom, I've had time
to think about it,

19:34.907 --> 19:36.175
and it's gonna be okay.

19:36.209 --> 19:38.177
I thought you said
you weren't feeling challenged

19:38.211 --> 19:39.246
in your regular school.

19:39.279 --> 19:41.648
And I'll make that
my new challenge.

19:41.681 --> 19:42.982
I'll do extra C.L.C.,

19:43.015 --> 19:44.917
audit some
junior college classes,

19:44.951 --> 19:46.386
take an immersion trip
to Montreal

19:46.419 --> 19:47.354
to work on my French.

19:48.955 --> 19:50.189
Michael Bolton

19:50.223 --> 19:51.858
offered me a partnership deal
for the restaurant,

19:51.891 --> 19:53.326
and I think
we should take it.

19:53.360 --> 19:54.594
What?

19:54.627 --> 19:56.363
I know it means
straying from our life plan,

19:56.396 --> 19:58.398
but we should make exceptions
for good opportunities.

19:58.431 --> 19:59.866
I want to own our house,

19:59.899 --> 20:02.068
and this deal
will let us do that.

20:05.805 --> 20:07.240
You're right.

20:07.274 --> 20:10.176
Maybe we can be less
strict with our plans.

20:10.209 --> 20:14.247
But we're not buying
this house.

20:18.485 --> 20:19.819
We'd like to buy
your house.

20:20.620 --> 20:22.121
You want to buy
 this house?

20:22.154 --> 20:24.257
But with
one stipulation.

20:25.124 --> 20:27.727
You get our son
into St. Orlando's.

20:27.760 --> 20:28.961
Your wife works there,
right?

20:30.263 --> 20:33.099
She gets our son in,
you've sold your house.

20:33.132 --> 20:34.767
We can work
something out.

20:35.101 --> 20:36.603
I'm going
to private school!

20:36.636 --> 20:38.605
I'm not in the garage,
but screw it!

20:38.638 --> 20:41.308
[ Chuckles ]

20:41.341 --> 20:42.442
Are we sure about this?

20:42.475 --> 20:43.876
You want
to own your own home,

20:43.910 --> 20:46.078
I want Evan
in private school.

20:46.112 --> 20:48.114
Michael Bolton
will get us both.

20:48.147 --> 20:51.451
**

20:56.456 --> 20:57.624
Dave: We did it!
We got the tape back.

20:57.657 --> 20:58.991
Are you gonna get in trouble
for throwing a rock

20:59.025 --> 21:00.226
through your
stepbrother's window?

21:00.259 --> 21:01.661
Eh, if things get heated
I can always fake a seizure.

21:01.694 --> 21:04.096
Guys, we're entering high school
on a win.

21:04.130 --> 21:05.998
Things are gonna be okay.

21:07.133 --> 21:08.301
Yeah!

21:13.473 --> 21:14.641
Divorce.

21:14.674 --> 21:15.942
What's going on?
Pack your things

21:15.975 --> 21:17.243
and say goodbye
to your friends.

21:17.276 --> 21:18.244
We're moving.

21:18.277 --> 21:20.380
Time to make new friends.

21:21.213 --> 21:22.515
Emery:
Hold that look, Eddie.

21:22.549 --> 21:24.183
I'm trying
to find the zoom.

21:24.216 --> 21:25.318
Ah, there it is.

21:25.352 --> 21:28.388
**
